I use postorder traversal to ensure children are processed before the parent.
After processing both subtrees, if the current node becomes a leaf and its value equals the target, we delete it by returning null. Otherwise, we return the node.

//code  Delete Leaves With a Given Value

class Solution {
    public TreeNode removeLeafNodes(TreeNode root, int target) {
         if(root != null) {
            root.left = removeLeafNodes(root.left, target);
            root.right = removeLeafNodes(root.right, target);
            if(root.left == null && root.right == null && root.val == target){
                return null;
            }
            return root;
        }
        return null;
    }
}
